{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/how-to-edit-scripts-with-your-favorite-editor/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Violentmonkey"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"bb4bb933-d660-571d-9543-a9b183c44cd6","html":"<p>For anyone who uses Violentmonkey, it is easy to find a way to edit a script like this:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/52e07bc04265f6628af77e2ed266053e/02cd5/editor-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/52e07bc04265f6628af77e2ed266053e/8e964/editor-1.webp 150w,\n/static/52e07bc04265f6628af77e2ed266053e/c85cb/editor-1.webp 300w,\n/static/52e07bc04265f6628af77e2ed266053e/e88ff/editor-1.webp 600w,\n/static/52e07bc04265f6628af77e2ed266053e/d77d0/editor-1.webp 821w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/52e07bc04265f6628af77e2ed266053e/8a4e8/editor-1.png 150w,\n/static/52e07bc04265f6628af77e2ed266053e/5a46d/editor-1.png 300w,\n/static/52e07bc04265f6628af77e2ed266053e/0a47e/editor-1.png 600w,\n/static/52e07bc04265f6628af77e2ed266053e/02cd5/editor-1.png 821w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/52e07bc04265f6628af77e2ed266053e/0a47e/editor-1.png\"\n            alt=\"editor 1\"\n            title=\"editor 1\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>However, it is really hard to make everyone love it. <em>A</em> probably likes a theme of <code class=\"language-text\">monokai</code>, while <em>B</em> prefers <code class=\"language-text\">eclipse</code>. <em>C</em> might use 2 spaces for indentation while <em>D</em> prefers tabs.</p>\n<p>It is impossible to satisfy every single user. Lots of configurations may be added for this, but are they really worth it? A user would have to face lots of choices before he could use it just as a script manager, or have to look for a simple option among lots of unrelated editor options. What is worse, the browser may inhibit some shortcuts or operations that a local editor can have. In other words, an editor inside Violentmonkey will never be as good as your favorite one.</p>\n<p>Here comes the question: How to edit my script with my favorite editor?</p>\n<h2 id=\"save-to-a-file\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#save-to-a-file\" aria-label=\"save to a file permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Save to a file</h2>\n<p>First, copy the script to your favorite editor and save it to a file.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/17a5d02e3af9acd5c40e180192fa9e07/6114d/editor-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.66666666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/17a5d02e3af9acd5c40e180192fa9e07/8e964/editor-2.webp 150w,\n/static/17a5d02e3af9acd5c40e180192fa9e07/c85cb/editor-2.webp 300w,\n/static/17a5d02e3af9acd5c40e180192fa9e07/e88ff/editor-2.webp 600w,\n/static/17a5d02e3af9acd5c40e180192fa9e07/7ac29/editor-2.webp 623w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/17a5d02e3af9acd5c40e180192fa9e07/8a4e8/editor-2.png 150w,\n/static/17a5d02e3af9acd5c40e180192fa9e07/5a46d/editor-2.png 300w,\n/static/17a5d02e3af9acd5c40e180192fa9e07/0a47e/editor-2.png 600w,\n/static/17a5d02e3af9acd5c40e180192fa9e07/6114d/editor-2.png 623w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/17a5d02e3af9acd5c40e180192fa9e07/0a47e/editor-2.png\"\n            alt=\"editor 2\"\n            title=\"editor 2\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>VIM is my favorite editor, and the script is saved at <code class=\"language-text\">D:/Source/vm-script.user.js</code>. Note that the script file must have a name ending with <code class=\"language-text\">.user.js</code>, otherwise won't be recognized by Violentmonkey.</p>\n<h2 id=\"install-a-local-script\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install-a-local-script\" aria-label=\"install a local script permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install a local script</h2>\n<p>First make sure the local script is named with a suffix of <code class=\"language-text\">.user.js</code>.</p>\n<p>There are two ways to install a local script:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><em>Easy way:</em> drag the file into the browser.</p>\n<p>It will be recognized by Violentmonkey and loaded in the confirmation page.</p>\n<p>Make sure <em>\"Allow access to file URLs\"</em> is checked in your <em>Chrome extension settings</em> (<code class=\"language-text\">chrome://extensions</code>).</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 420px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bf23974b6eeaef641a71bf08d1f2dd1c/d10fb/editor-6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 33.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/bf23974b6eeaef641a71bf08d1f2dd1c/8e964/editor-6.webp 150w,\n/static/bf23974b6eeaef641a71bf08d1f2dd1c/c85cb/editor-6.webp 300w,\n/static/bf23974b6eeaef641a71bf08d1f2dd1c/ce09e/editor-6.webp 420w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/bf23974b6eeaef641a71bf08d1f2dd1c/8a4e8/editor-6.png 150w,\n/static/bf23974b6eeaef641a71bf08d1f2dd1c/5a46d/editor-6.png 300w,\n/static/bf23974b6eeaef641a71bf08d1f2dd1c/d10fb/editor-6.png 420w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/bf23974b6eeaef641a71bf08d1f2dd1c/d10fb/editor-6.png\"\n            alt=\"editor 6\"\n            title=\"editor 6\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong> that due to a <a href=\"#known-issues\">known issue</a>, the <em>easy way</em> <strong>won't work for Firefox users</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><em>Hard way:</em> start a local HTTP server, then open the local script with a URL like <code class=\"language-text\">http://localhost:8080/my-script.user.js</code>.</p>\n<p>One of the best way is to use node/npm's <a href=\"https://github.com/indexzero/http-server#readme\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">indexzero/http-server</a>. If you have it installed, just type <code class=\"language-text\">http-server -c5</code> at the directory of your script to start a server.</p>\n<p>Make sure the hostname is <code class=\"language-text\">localhost</code> and the script name ends with <code class=\"language-text\">.user.js</code>.</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong> that due to a <a href=\"https://github.com/violentmonkey/violentmonkey/issues/460#issuecomment-434335758\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">known issue</a>, the <em>hard way</em> needs to handle caching. In <code class=\"language-text\">http-server -c5</code> option <code class=\"language-text\">-c5</code> sets cache time for max-age header to 5 seconds, thus forcing a browser to query the server URL every 5 seconds. The caching can be disabled with <code class=\"language-text\">-c-1</code> option.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/661dce4756c0ba64899cbb919da56f8b/02cd5/editor-3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/661dce4756c0ba64899cbb919da56f8b/8e964/editor-3.webp 150w,\n/static/661dce4756c0ba64899cbb919da56f8b/c85cb/editor-3.webp 300w,\n/static/661dce4756c0ba64899cbb919da56f8b/e88ff/editor-3.webp 600w,\n/static/661dce4756c0ba64899cbb919da56f8b/d77d0/editor-3.webp 821w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/661dce4756c0ba64899cbb919da56f8b/8a4e8/editor-3.png 150w,\n/static/661dce4756c0ba64899cbb919da56f8b/5a46d/editor-3.png 300w,\n/static/661dce4756c0ba64899cbb919da56f8b/0a47e/editor-3.png 600w,\n/static/661dce4756c0ba64899cbb919da56f8b/02cd5/editor-3.png 821w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/661dce4756c0ba64899cbb919da56f8b/0a47e/editor-3.png\"\n            alt=\"editor 3\"\n            title=\"editor 3\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Make sure the <code class=\"language-text\">track local file</code> option is checked and then confirm installation.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c24d0bc496b005979d19eb4d4d6db0b5/02cd5/editor-4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/c24d0bc496b005979d19eb4d4d6db0b5/8e964/editor-4.webp 150w,\n/static/c24d0bc496b005979d19eb4d4d6db0b5/c85cb/editor-4.webp 300w,\n/static/c24d0bc496b005979d19eb4d4d6db0b5/e88ff/editor-4.webp 600w,\n/static/c24d0bc496b005979d19eb4d4d6db0b5/d77d0/editor-4.webp 821w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/c24d0bc496b005979d19eb4d4d6db0b5/8a4e8/editor-4.png 150w,\n/static/c24d0bc496b005979d19eb4d4d6db0b5/5a46d/editor-4.png 300w,\n/static/c24d0bc496b005979d19eb4d4d6db0b5/0a47e/editor-4.png 600w,\n/static/c24d0bc496b005979d19eb4d4d6db0b5/02cd5/editor-4.png 821w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/c24d0bc496b005979d19eb4d4d6db0b5/0a47e/editor-4.png\"\n            alt=\"editor 4\"\n            title=\"editor 4\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"edit-and-sync\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#edit-and-sync\" aria-label=\"edit and sync permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Edit and sync</h2>\n<p>After installation, the confirmation page will keep watching the file before the page is closed. Once the file is changed, the new version will be installed automatically. As a result, you edit the script in your favorite editor, and the changes are synced to Violentmonkey immediately.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/421f4c24f117d74eacd0208b1870bfb9/02cd5/editor-5.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/421f4c24f117d74eacd0208b1870bfb9/8e964/editor-5.webp 150w,\n/static/421f4c24f117d74eacd0208b1870bfb9/c85cb/editor-5.webp 300w,\n/static/421f4c24f117d74eacd0208b1870bfb9/e88ff/editor-5.webp 600w,\n/static/421f4c24f117d74eacd0208b1870bfb9/d77d0/editor-5.webp 821w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/421f4c24f117d74eacd0208b1870bfb9/8a4e8/editor-5.png 150w,\n/static/421f4c24f117d74eacd0208b1870bfb9/5a46d/editor-5.png 300w,\n/static/421f4c24f117d74eacd0208b1870bfb9/0a47e/editor-5.png 600w,\n/static/421f4c24f117d74eacd0208b1870bfb9/02cd5/editor-5.png 821w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/421f4c24f117d74eacd0208b1870bfb9/0a47e/editor-5.png\"\n            alt=\"editor 5\"\n            title=\"editor 5\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"known-issues\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#known-issues\" aria-label=\"known issues permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Known issues</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>In Firefox Violentmonkey is not allowed to access local files, so we have to start a local HTTP server for tracking. See <a href=\"https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1266960\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this on bugzilla</a>.</li>\n<li>The older the file is, the more seldom a browser will query it. See <a href=\"https://github.com/violentmonkey/violentmonkey/issues/460#issuecomment-434335758\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this Violentmonkey's issue</a>.</li>\n</ul>","fields":{"tagSlugs":["/tags/editor/","/tags/crx/","/tags/nex/","/tags/oex/","/tags/mx/"],"type":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to edit scripts with your favorite editor?","tags":["editor","crx","nex","oex","mx"],"date":"2017-03-14T14:37:09.000Z","sidebar":null},"tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#save-to-a-file\">Save to a file</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#install-a-local-script\">Install a local script</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#edit-and-sync\">Edit and sync</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#known-issues\">Known issues</a></li>\n</ul>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/how-to-edit-scripts-with-your-favorite-editor/","type":"posts"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1878747374","2344890832","3365866253","3486277714"]}